<emphasis id="B95A5142FFC4FFE1FF3C4F47A211FA00" bold="true" box="[189,334,1383,1409]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B918D50FFC4FFE1FF6B4FB6A13CFA30" blockId="8.[189,1399,1430,1853]" box="[234,611,1430,1457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B95A5142FFC4FFE1FF6B4FB6A29AFA31" bold="true" box="[234,453,1430,1456]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Light microscopy</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC4FFE1FE544FB6A104FA30" box="[469,603,1430,1457]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 58–82</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B918D50FFC4FFE1FF3C4F9AA022F8BC" blockId="8.[189,1399,1430,1853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Valves broadly elliptic-lanceolate with clearly convex margins gradually tapering towards the broadly rounded, non-protracted apices. Valve dimensions (n = 30): length 
<quantity id="4CD620B5FFC4FFE1FC504FFFA761FA78" box="[977,1086,1503,1529]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12 µm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CD620B5FFC4FFE1FB144FFEA67FFA78" box="[1173,1312,1502,1529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="4.15" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.8">3.8–4.5 µm</quantity>
. Raphe valve (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC4FFE1FE8C4C22A2C6F99C" box="[269,409,1538,1565]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 58–70</figureCitation>
): axial area narrow, linear, not widening towards central area. Central area forming a rectangular to bow-tie-shaped fascia with occasionally one to several shortened striae near the valve margins (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC4FFE1FEA94C6AA286F9E4" box="[296,473,1610,1637]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 62–64, 68</figureCitation>
). Raphe straight with almost indistinct, straight proximal endings. Distal fissures not discernible in LM. Transapical striae weakly radiate near the central area, becoming more radiate towards the apices, 
<quantity id="4CD620B5FFC4FFE1FE2E4CB3A145F92D" box="[431,538,1682,1709]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.128" metricValueMax="8.636" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="32.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="30.0">30–34 in</quantity>
<quantity id="4CD620B5FFC4FFE1FDA54CB3A127F92C" box="[548,632,1683,1709]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
. Areolae not discernible in LM. Rapheless valve (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC4FFE1FB5D4CB2A635F92C" box="[1244,1386,1682,1709]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 71–82</figureCitation>
): axial area very narrow, linear distinctly widening towards the central area. Central area rounded to apically elliptical, bow-tie shaped widening towards the valve margins, almost forming a fascia. Regularly, shortened striae present near the valve margins. Transapical striae weakly radiate throughout becoming more radiate towards the apices, 
<quantity id="4CD620B5FFC4FFE1FD3B4D02A07DF8BD" box="[698,802,1826,1852]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.763" metricValueMax="9.144" metricValueMin="8.382" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="34.5" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="33.0">33–36 in</quantity>
<quantity id="4CD620B5FFC4FFE1FCA84D03A026F8BC" box="[809,889,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B918D50FFC4FFE1FF6B4D45A1A1F801" blockId="8.[189,1399,1893,2027]" box="[234,766,1893,1920]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B95A5142FFC4FFE1FF6B4D45A13FF8FE" bold="true" box="[234,608,1893,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Scanning electron microscopy</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC4FFE1FDF14D45A1A9F801" box="[624,758,1893,1920]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 83–85</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B918D50FFC4FFE3FF3C4DA9A0F0FE7C" blockId="8.[189,1399,1893,2027]" lastBlockId="10.[189,1399,267,509]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Raphe valve (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC4FFE1FEE14DA9A2E6F822" box="[352,441,1929,1955]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
): striae uniseriate, composed of small, rounded to rectangular areolae, the largest areolae located close to the axial area. Number of areolae per stria diminishing towards the axial area. Near valve margins, last areola transapically elongated, slit-like. A row of slit-like areolae present on the mantle. Raphe branches almost straight. Proximal raphe endings straight, drop-like expanded (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC6FFE3FA904B2BA636FEA7" box="[1297,1385,267,294]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
). Distal endings short, weakly drop-like expanded. Rapheless valve (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC6FFE3FC664B0FA72CFECB" box="[999,1139,303,330]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs 84–85</figureCitation>
): central area slightly depressed, forming a weak pseudoraphe (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC6FFE3FD394B73A04BFEEC" box="[696,788,339,365]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). Striae uniseriate composed of small, rounded to rectangular and transapically elongated areolae (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC6FFE3FD6F4B57A01BFE10" box="[750,836,375,401]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). Slit-like areolae present near the valve margins and onto the mantle (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC6FFE3FE344BBBA152FE34" box="[437,525,411,437]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). In the central area, several slit-like areolae visible near the valve margin. Internally areolae transapically elongated, covered by individual perforated hymenes (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC6FFE3FB3B4B9FA64CFE5B" box="[1210,1299,447,474]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
). Virgae slightly raised. Small silica bars separating the areolae (
<figureCitation id="131591D5FFC6FFE3FCCB4BC3A0FDFE7C" box="[842,930,482,509]" captionStart="Figs 58–85" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[305,1283,265,1814]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 58–85. Psammothidium confusoneglectum Kopalová, Zidarova &amp; Van de Vijver sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 58–70. LM views of raphe valves. 71–82. LM views of rapheless valves. 83. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 84. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 85. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
